To selling your own eCommerce website system to clients, and need to:
•	Control license per client
•	Activate by domain
•	Expire license (optional)
•	Suspend client access
•	Control update access
•	Track activation history
A client license management system need 3 tables:
clients
licenses
license_activations
1️⃣ 	Clients Table
	php artisan make:migration create_clients_table
Schema::create('clients', function (Blueprint $table) {
$table->id();
$table->string('name');
$table->string('email')->unique();
$table->string('phone')->nullable();
$table->string('company_name')->nullable();
$table->timestamps();
});
2️⃣ 	Licenses Table (Main Control Table)
	php artisan make:migration create_licenses_table
Schema::create('licenses', function (Blueprint $table) {
$table->id();

$table->unsignedBigInteger('client_id');

$table->string('license_key')->unique();
$table->string('domain')->nullable(); // main domain
$table->integer('activation_limit')->default(1);

$table->enum('plan', ['lifetime', '1_year', '6_month']);
$table->timestamp('expires_at')->nullable();

$table->enum('status', ['active', 'expired', 'suspended'])
->default('active');

$table->boolean('update_access')->default(true);

$table->timestamps();

$table->foreign('client_id')
->references('id')->on('clients')
->onDelete('cascade');
});
3️⃣ 	License Activations Table (Domain Control)
	php artisan make:migration create_license_activations_table
Schema::create('license_activations', function (Blueprint $table) {
$table->id();

$table->unsignedBigInteger('license_id');
$table->string('domain');
$table->string('ip_address')->nullable();
$table->timestamp('activated_at')->nullable();

$table->timestamps();

$table->foreign('license_id')
->references('id')->on('licenses')
->onDelete('cascade');

$table->unique(['license_id', 'domain']);
});
How This System Works
When client installs your script:
1.	They enter license key
2.	Your system:
o	Checks license exists
o	Checks status = active
o	Checks expiration
o	Checks activation_limit
3.	Saves domain into license_activations
4.	If suspended → system stops working




